<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CSUN WINNING STREAK IN VOLLEYBALL HITS 50 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cal State Northridge won its 50th consecutive California Collegiate Athletic 
Assn. home volleyball match by sweeping Cal State Los Angeles, 15-1, 15-6, 
15-11, in less than an hour. 
</P>
<P>
Northridge (12-8, 2-2 in CCAA matches), tied with Regis College for fifth in 
the latest NCAA Division II poll, had a team hitting percentage of .282, while 
Cal State L. A. (3-11, 0-3) struggled with a .014 hitting percentage. 
</P>
<P>
Freshman outside hitter Patty Fitzsimmons and junior outside hitter Marianne 
Dixon led Northridge with seven kills each. 
</P>
<P>
Nancy Nichols added six kills and sophomore setter Karen Scholl had 18 assists. 
</P>
<P>
Northridge Coach Walt Ker cleared his bench after the first game, and reserves 
played extensively in the final two games. 
</P>
<P>
Junior outside hitter Cecilia Casillas provided much of what offense Cal State 
L. A. could muster with five kills. 
</P>
<P>
In other volleyball matches: 
</P>
<P>
Grand Canyon d. Cal Lutheran, 15-4, 15-12, 15-7 -- Cal Lutheran tumbled to 0-16 
after a loss to visiting Grand Canyon, 23-5 and ranked eighth in National Assn. 
of Intercollegiate Athletics poll. 
</P>
<P>
Jenifer Larson led the Regals with nine kills. Larson entered the match ranked 
fifth in NAIA District 3 with a .370 hitting percentage, but she managed only a 
.195 percentage against Grand Canyon. Brenda Lee had four digs and four blocks, 
and setter Debbie Wolfe recorded 15 assists for CLU. 
</P>
<P>
Theresa Kennedy led Grand Canyon with eight kills. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
The Master's 11, California Maritime 0 -- Jim Rickard scored three goals and 
Chris Bingman and Russ Spencer each added two for Master's in the nonconference 
match at home. 
</P>
<P>
The other goals were scored by Jorge Barba, Jon Neidnagel, Mike Rozsa and Olin 
Bakke, as Master's, the NAIA's 15th-ranked team, improved to 9-3-3. 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark 4, Hancock 1 -- Eric Gunter scored two goals and Billy Kranz and Richy 
Rungaitis each added a goal for Moorpark (5-2-1, 1-0-0) in a Western State 
Conference match at Hancock. 
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark 4, El Camino 0 -- Moorpark (10-1-1, 4-1-1) closed a seven-game home 
stand by shutting out El Camino in a South Coast Conference game. 
</P>
<P>
Stephanie Gainey, Kristin Mealiffe, Nikky Argenti and Wendy Berna all scored 
for Moorpark. Goalie Rustie Stevens had seven saves in recording her fourth 
shutout. 
</P>
<P>
WATER POLO 
</P>
<P>
Cuesta 18, Valley 7 -- Both teams were undefeated in the Western State 
Conference, but visiting Cuesta (3-0 in league play) routed Valley (10-8, 2-1) 
behind Jamie Stuart's four goals. Nick Kaufman scored two goals for Valley. 
</P>
</TEXT>
