SOUTHERN SECTION ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CRUZ'S RETURN SPARKS THOUSAND OAKS, 21-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL OLSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ronnie Cruz returned the opening kickoff of the second half 73 yards for a 
touchdown to break open a scoreless Marmonte League game Friday night and lead 
Thousand Oaks to a 21-0 victory over host Camarillo. 
</P>
<P>
The shutout was the third of the season for the Lancers (5-0-1, 3-0 in league 
play). 
</P>
<P>
Sophomore Dave Acosta recovered a muffed punt at the Camarillo 35-yard line to 
set up another Lancer score in the third quarter. Thousand Oaks quarterback 
Scott Peterson, who completed only one of nine passes, tossed a 35-yard 
touchdown pass to Jim Magallanes on a fourth-and-10 play. 
</P>
<P>
Reserve fullback Brian Sturges gained 56 of the 59 yards on a seven-play 
Thousand Oaks drive and scored on a four-yard run midway through the fourth 
quarter for the last touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
In a defensive battle, Thousand Oaks had 133 yards in offense and Camarillo 
(2-4, 1-2) gained 75 total yards. Camarillo linebacker Scott Foster registered 
four solo sacks for minus-25 yards to lead the Scorpion defense. 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks fullback Chris Foster (24 yards in three carries) left the game 
after less than three minutes with an injury to his left knee and did not 
return. 
</P>
<P>
Camarillo running back Tim Cornish led the Scorpions in rushing with 28 yards 
in eight carries. PAUL OLSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
