<P>
City Western League 
</P>
<P>
Kearny 22, USDHS 6 -- Kearny built a 22-0 lead after the first series of the 
second half to win this game between two favorites to win the league title. 
Darnay Scott caught a 17-yard touchdown pass and a two-point conversion for 
Kearny (5-1, 1-0). Scott also had an interception when USDHS was threatening in 
the second half. The Kearny defense held Bryan Duplesis to 45 yards on 18 
carries. Duplesis was averaging 101 yards per game. Kearny quarterback Tommy 
Rawlins scored twice on one-yard runs and threw for another score. USDHS is 
(4-2, 0-1). 
</P>
