City Eastern League 
</P>
<P>
Point Loma 27, Serra 0 -- Officials called the game with 2:41 remaining when 
Serra receiver Jason Crawford sustained a neck injury and trainers were unable 
to move him from the field. 
</P>
<P>
Crawford was eventually taken by ambulance to Sharp Memorial Hospital where 
X-rays showed there was no fracture. 
</P>
<P>
A hospital spokesman said Crawford, 17, "probably suffered no more than a 
bruise." 
</P>
<P>
No. 5 Point Loma (3-3, 1-0) was led by running back Marlon Manassa, who rushed 
for 96 yards and three second-half touchdowns, and by quarterback Dan White, 
who threw for 267 yards and one second-half touchdown in break a 0-0 halftime 
deficit. White was 14 of 20. J.J. Stokes caught four passes and on defense 
intercepted two and deflected two. 
</P>
