<HEADLINE>
<P>
CASTING QUESTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re the Oct. 7 article on the movie "War Party": 
</P>
<P>
Let me see if I understand this. In the entire United States of American were 
there no actors other than Kevin Dillon (a white) and Billy Wirth (whose 
great-great grandmother was American Indian) qualified to play the leading 
American Indian roles in this film? 
</P>
<P>
I realize that name recognition is important to producers, but surely these 
fine young actors could have played the leading white roles. 
</P>
<P>
I wonder if it has occurred to the film's producers to contribute some 
(probably tax-deductible) portion of the film's proceeds to improve the 
possibility that the people they are exploiting will survive into adulthood? 
</P>
<P>
EVA SNIDER, Pasadena 
</P>
</TEXT>
