CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SACRAMENTO; 
</P>
<P>
BAIL IS RAISED FOR 'BABY THAO' SUSPECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Debra Marie Lucas, accused of kidnaping newborn "Baby Thao" from a Sacramento 
hospital maternity ward, appeared in court Friday where her bail was raised to 
$100,000. Deputy Dist. Atty. Jan Scully, arguing for the bail increase from 
$15,000, said Lucas might flee because she faces a possible prison term and has 
strong ties to the Oakland area. "Her flight risk, we think, is substantial," 
Scully said. Lucas, 36, is being held in the Sacramento County Jail. If 
convicted of kidnaping, she could be sentenced to 16 years in prison. Lucas is 
charged with kidnaping Baby Thao from his mother, a Hmong immigrant from Laos, 
at Mercy General Hospital. 
</P>
