<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: CAMP PENDLETON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Escondido man died Friday when the car he was driving veered off Interstate 
5 and slammed into a parked van that burst into flames, a California Highway 
Patrol spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The accident that killed Mark Edward Jovin, 32, occurred about 2:30 a.m. on I-5 
south of Basilone Road, CHP Officer Gary Kiger said. Witnesses said Jovin was 
traveling north, weaving in and out of traffic, when he hit the abandoned van 
parked on the east shoulder of the freeway. Jovin was dead at the scene, Deputy 
Coroner Chuck Kelly said. 
</P>
