<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: INFORMANT'S TIP LEADS POLICE TO STOLEN 
GOODS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sheriff's deputies found $315,000 worth of home electronic equipment, clothing 
and furniture that had been stolen from several cargo shipments in a Lynwood 
warehouse on Long beach Boulevard -- but they did not find the thieves who 
stole it. 
</P>
<P>
An informant's tip led to the discovery of the merchandise that had been stolen 
in in Carson, Long Beach and the Los Angeles Harbor Area since August, Deputy 
Pat Hunter said. 
</P>
