<HEADLINE>
<P>
HUBBARD RUNS, PASSES CYPRESS TO 13-0 VICTORY OVER EL DORADO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bobby Hubbard passed for one touchdown and ran for another to lead Cypress High 
School to a 13-0 victory over El Dorado Friday in the Empire League opener for 
both teams at Western High School. 
</P>
<P>
After a fumble recovery on the El Dorado 27-yard line by Richard Parsons, 
Cypress (3-3, 1-0) took seven plays before Hubbard scored on a one-yard run 
with 7 minutes 15 seconds left in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
Hubbard, who completed 15 of 26 passes for 141 yards, connected on a 10-yard 
scoring pass to tight end Sean Gibson with three seconds remaining in the half. 
</P>
<P>
Cypress held El Dorado (0-1, 0-6) to 54 yards in total offense. 
</P>
<P>
Gibson caught six passes for 70 yards, and running back Brian Dawson had 49 
yards in 15 carries to lead all rushers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
