<HEADLINE>
<P>
LA HABRA DEFENSE REGROUPS AND PACES 21-17 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LA HABRA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
La Habra High School's defensive unit bounced back from last week's 55-14 loss 
to Perris, leading the Highlanders to a 21-17 Freeway League victory over Buena 
Park at La Habra Stadium Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
La Habra's defense, which gave up 555 yards to Perris last week, held Buena 
Park to 57 yards in the second half to preserve the victory. La Habra is 3-3 
overall and 1-0 in league play. Buena Park is 1-5 overall and 0-1 in league. 
</P>
<P>
La Habra broke a 14-14 tie on a four-yard touchdown pass from Mark Moreno to 
Mark Brown on the last play of the first half. 
</P>
<P>
Moreno was 10 of 14 for 89 yards and one touchdown. Brown was La Habra's 
leading rusher with 116 yards in 21 carries. 
</P>
<P>
After a 24-yard field goal by Hugo Melendez cut the La Habra lead to 21-17 in 
the third quarter, Buena Park had the ball in La Habra territory three more 
times but failed to score. 
</P>
</TEXT>
