<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Technology Marketing Inc., Irvine, reported that net income for the second 
quarter of fiscal 1990 fell to $18,483 from $222,182 for the same period last 
year. Revenue for the quarter ended Aug. 31 declined 29%, to $2 million from 
$2.9 million. 
</P>
<P>
For the six-month period, the computer products company recorded a net profit 
of $264,141, contrasted with a net profit of $625,343 a year earlier. Revenue 
dropped 25%, to $4.6 million from $6.2 million. 
</P>
<P>
Gerald T. Hudspeth, president and chief executive, said that "although our last 
eight quarters have been profitable, the August ending quarter reflects 
concerns about recent delays and overall cautiousness of our customers in 
releasing new equipment and contract orders." 
</P>
</TEXT>
